bce6cba1-097e-57c4-a4d2-e0c866fff77b,tg:rubgr:92,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"Fall of Icarus. a) Drawing, pen & wash by Hans Bol, Hamburg Kunsthalle, repr. [H. Gerard] Franz, [= Hans Bol als Landschaftszeichner], Jahrbuch des Kunsthistorischen Institutes der Universität Graz, I, 1965, [pp. 19-67], pl.112, neither signed nor dated, placed by Franz in [onleesbaar] among drawings of early 1580s. Showing Daedalus & Icarus. Peasant ploughing, 2 shepherds with flock of sheep [...];  b) Franz, pls. 147; c) Franz, pl. 171 engraving HBol inve. combining motifs from pl. 112 & 147, but closer to 112; d) 183, Fall of Icarus, Mayer van Bergh; e) pl.185 roundel Musée van Maerlant roundel.",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>Fall of Icarus. a) Drawing, pen & wash by Hans Bol, Hamburg Kunsthalle, repr. [H. Gerard] Franz, [= Hans Bol als Landschaftszeichner], Jahrbuch des Kunsthistorischen Institutes der Universität Graz, I, 1965, [pp. 19-67], pl.112, neither signed nor dated, placed by Franz in [onleesbaar] among drawings of early 1580s. Showing Daedalus & Icarus. Peasant ploughing, 2 shepherds with flock of sheep [...];  b) Franz, pls. 147; c) Franz, pl. 171 engraving HBol inve. combining motifs from pl. 112 & 147, but closer to 112; d) 183, Fall of Icarus, Mayer van Bergh; e) pl.185 roundel Musée van Maerlant roundel.</content>
